# Lesson Player System

The Lesson Player is where actual learning happens.

It is the most critical execution environment in LexMastery.

---

# Product Vision

The Lesson Player must:

- Deliver content clearly and progressively
- Track learning in real-time
- Enable active engagement
- Support AI-assisted explanations
- Work fully offline (when downloaded)

It is not a reader.

It is an interactive learning engine.

---

# Lesson Types

Supported formats:

- Text Lessons
- Video Lessons (future-ready)
- Mixed Media Lessons
- Interactive Lessons
- Quiz Embedded Lessons

Each lesson must declare its type explicitly.

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

LessonPlayerController (Riverpod)

↓

LessonPlayerState

↓

LessonsRepository

↓

Local Cache + Remote API

---

# State Management

LessonPlayerState includes:

- loading
- error
- ready
- playing
- paused
- completed
- offline

Core Data:

- lessonContent
- currentProgress
- lastPosition
- bookmarks
- notes
- AIContext

Never use boolean flags like isPlaying or isLoading.

---

# Progress Tracking

Progress must be tracked:

- per paragraph
- per section
- per lesson completion

Updates must be:

- real-time
- debounced
- synced to server

---

# Navigation Rules

Lesson Player supports:

- next lesson
- previous lesson
- module exit
- resume last position

Back navigation must preserve state.

---

# AI Integration

AI supports:

- instant explanations of paragraphs
- legal concept breakdown
- example generation
- clarification on demand

AI responses must be contextual to lesson position.

---

# Offline Behaviour

Lesson must be fully functional offline if downloaded:

- content readable
- progress tracked
- notes available
- bookmarks usable

AI features disabled offline.

---

# Notes System

Users can:

- highlight text
- attach notes
- save key points

Notes must be:

- synced
- searchable
- linked to lesson position

---

# Bookmarks

Users can bookmark:

- paragraphs
- sections
- full lessons

Bookmarks must persist across devices.

---

# API Contracts

GET /lessons/{id}

GET /lessons/{id}/content

POST /lessons/progress

POST /lessons/notes

POST /lessons/bookmarks

---

# Analytics Events

lesson_open

lesson_progress_update

lesson_complete

lesson_note_created

lesson_bookmark_added

lesson_ai_query

---

# UI Composition Rules

Lesson Player must include:

- Progress indicator
- Scroll-based navigation
- Sticky AI assistant button
- Notes panel
- Bookmark action
- Next/Previous controls

---

# UX Rules

- Never overwhelm user with AI prompts
- Keep reading flow uninterrupted
- AI must be optional, not intrusive
- Progress feedback must be subtle

---

# Error Handling

If lesson fails:

- fallback to cached version
- allow retry
- preserve last position

Never reset progress unexpectedly.

---

# Performance

- Content must render instantly (<200ms shell load)
- Lazy load sections
- Avoid full rebuilds on scroll

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- screen readers
- reading focus mode
- font scaling
- distraction-free mode

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

LessonPlayerController

Progress tracking logic

Notes system

Widget Tests:

Lesson rendering

Progress UI

Notes UI

Integration Tests:

Full lesson flow

Offline lesson usage

AI interaction flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating lesson features:

- Always preserve reading position
- Always implement progress tracking
- Always support offline mode
- Always integrate AI context-aware assistance
- Never break reading flow with intrusive UI